      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Goblins, you say? Always with the little furry things, aren't you? Like a particularly plump, slightly grumpy goblin hoarding shiny pebbles. But fine, about your lab, a good, sturdy dog, not some skittish goblin pup.\n\nFor an aging lab, you want something that supports muscle mass without making him feel like he's swallowed a whole pile of goblin-sized rocks. Generally, when you're looking at high-protein senior food, you want a ratio that leans heavily on the protein, but the fat needs to be there to keep those old joints happy—you don't want him moving like a goblin who's tripped over a particularly sharp root.\n\nI'd suggest looking for a protein content in the range of **28% to 35%** of the total ingredients. That's a solid foundation, like a well-built goblin warren, strong enough to keep the bad guys out.\n\nAs for the fat, you don't want it too high, or he'll start looking like a goblin who's been gorging on fermented swamp berries—too much bloat! Aiming for **15% to 20%** of fat",
